A MAN who allegedly robbed two paramedics of their cellphones and cash at a tourist destination in Howick Falls, KZN has been arrested.The suspect allegedly held the two women at knifepoint and demanded they give him their cellphones and money on Tuesday. However, the man&rsquo;s alleged crime spree came to an end in the early hours of yesterday morning when cops pounced on him. ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring commended the Howick cops for their swift arrest.&ldquo;Following information received during investigations, the police raided a shack in the Shiyabazali informal settlement &shy;located close to where the robbery &shy;occurred,&rdquo; he said. He said the suspect was arrested and the two cellphones were recovered.&ldquo;The knife used by the suspect to threaten the paramedics was also recovered,&rdquo; he said. Meiring said ER24 paramedics were often standby at the tourist attraction.&ldquo;There were no tourists or visitors at the spot at the time of the incident,&rdquo; he said.Describing the robbery he said: &ldquo;The two paramedics were inside the vehicle when they were approached by a young man holding a large knife. &ldquo;The man ordered them to look down and give him their cellphones and the cash in their wallets. He also asked them to remove their SIM cards and memory cards from their phones before giving them to him.&rdquo;KZN cops spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said: &ldquo;We can confirm that a 20-year-old suspect was arrested at Shiyabazali informal settlement in Howick. He will appear in the Howick Magistrates Court soon.&rdquo;